#Text=The Phoenix Suns ( 14 - 31 ) defeated the Atlanta Hawks ( 26 - 19 ) 98 - 95 on Saturday night .
#Text=This was expected to be a high - scoring game , but the two offenses really struggled with both rosters being extremely shorthanded .
#Text=That doesn’t mean it wasn’t a good game though , as the action in the closing minutes was just fantastic .
#Text=Archie Goodwin was the hero , as he hit the game - winning three with less than a second to go .
#Text=What won the game for the Suns was the rebounding though , as they snatched down 52 boards to the Hawks 43 .
#Text=Both teams shot 40 percent from the field and took a combined 58 three - pointers .
#Text=Atlanta actually came into this game as a double - digit favorite , so it ended up being quite the upset .
#Text=The Atlanta Hawks had to play this game without Paul Millsap and it 's obvious with this result how important he is to this team .
#Text=Atlanta struggled mightily on the offensive end of the floor , as the post players for the Suns dominated this game .
#Text=Kent Bazemore kept his team in it with some huge shots late and finished with 21 points and six rebounds .
#Text=Al Horford had a nice all - around game as well , as he tallied nine points , 16 rebounds , five assists and two blocks in the defeat .
#Text=Dennis Schroder once again played down the stretch and scored 16 points with Jeff Teague 's continuing to struggle .
#Text=The Hawks will look to play better in their next game on Monday against the Denver Nuggets .
#Text=The Suns played with some fire here for the first time in quite a while and the future is bright even though the present is dark .
#Text=This was only their second win in their last 16 games , and it was easily their best defensive performance .
#Text=Tyson Chandler was just a monster down low , as he snatched 17 rebounds in the first half alone .
#Text=Chandler finished the game with 13 points , 27 rebounds and five assists in a spectacular performance .
#Text=All the starters played well here , as all five players scored in double - figures and combined for 84 points .
#Text=Archie Goodwin led the team with 24 points and has been filling in brilliantly for Brandon Knight , who is dealing with an abductor strain .
#Text=Alex Len was a beast down low as well , as he amassed 16 points , 12 rebounds and five assists .
#Text=Phoenix will look to build on this win when they take on the Philadelphia 76ers in their next game on Tuesday .
